summary.para: Gets a value that indicates whether a generic method contains unassigned generic type parameters.

value.para: if the current method contains unassigned generic type parameters; otherwise .

remarks.para: The default behavior, when not overridden in a derived class, is to return . In other words, by default, derived classes do not support generics.

In order to invoke a generic method, there must be no generic type definitions or open constructed types in the type arguments of the method itself, or in any enclosing types. If the property returns , the method cannot be invoked.

The property searches recursively for type parameters. For example, it returns for any method in an open type , even though the method itself is not generic. Contrast this with the behavior of the property, which returns for such a method.
For a list of the invariant conditions for terms specific to generic methods, see the property. For a list of the invariant conditions for other terms used in generic reflection, see the property.

summary.para: Returns an array of objects that represent the type arguments of a generic method or the type parameters of a generic method definition.

returns.para: An array of objects that represent the type arguments of a generic method or the type parameters of a generic method definition. Returns an empty array if the current method is not a generic method.

remarks.para: The default behavior, when not overridden in a derived class, is to throw . In other words, derived classes do not support generics by default.
The elements of the returned array are in the order in which they appear in the list of type parameters for the generic method.

term.para: If the current method is a closed constructed method (that is, the property returns ), the array returned by the method contains the types that have been assigned to the generic type parameters of the generic method definition.
If the current method is a generic method definition, the array contains the type parameters.

If the current method is an open constructed method (that is, the property returns ) in which specific types have been assigned to some type parameters and type parameters of enclosing generic types have been assigned to other type parameters, the array contains both types and type parameters. Use the property to tell them apart.

remarks.para: For a list of the invariant conditions for terms specific to generic methods, see the property. For a list of the invariant conditions for other terms used in generic reflection, see the property.

exception.para: Default behavior when not overridden in a derived class.
